Anonymous Tue 04 Jun 2024 14:04:19 No.66321675 Report
Quoted By: >>66321803 >>66322869 >>66326340
All the discussion about content makes me want to say this even if it's going to piss some people off. If you are an aspiring writefag/drawfag then do not, I repeat do not, get into the hobby with the intention of making content 'for' the thread. The thread is under no obligation to notice you, the thread is under no obligation to like your work, the thread might bury your update post under a hundred posts of garbage for no reason at all, the thread might shower attention on a two post smutty greentext and ignore your ten thousand words of prose, the thread might also give you a bunch of replies on your first work and none on your second. I know we all like to act like /hmofa/ is a group of highly cultured individuals that are of a higher caliber than the furry community, smoking our cigars and sipping our whiskey while reading the latest hmofa smut, but these days the thread acts like a bunch of schizophrenic coomers more often than not. It's not 2020 anymore, someone talking unprompted about your work is more the exception than the rule.

If you want to make something then the first and only person you should be worried about pleasing is yourself. Don't put your blood, sweat, and tears into making something exclusively for a bunch of anonymous posters on the internet because when they end up not giving a shit about that thing you spent hours/days/weeks making, and it will eventually happen, it's going to kill you on the inside. So if you genuinely want to write about a guy falling in love with his childhood friend tomboy wolf gf then by all means, go ahead and write it.
